C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Application\acu\API221MotionCtrl\API221MotionCtrl.c
      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @brief       Communications to control a remote motor or motor-controlled device.
      4           *
      5           * @details     The same API221MotionCtrl module is used on the client and the server.
      6           *                  Client Definitions:
      7           *                      API221_CLIENT_FEATURE should be ENABLED
      8           *                      API221_SERVER_FEATURE should be DISABLED
      9           *                  Server Definitions:
     10           *                      API221_CLIENT_FEATURE should be DISABLED
     11           *                      API221_SERVER_FEATURE should be ENABLED
     12           *              Using the same module on the client and server helps ensure that the client and
     13           *              server are using the same type and version of the API.
     14           *
     15           *              API221MotionCtrl allows each client to control one or more motor control servers
     16           *              that each controls one or more motor. For each of the system motors, the API
     17           *              manages four types of data:
     18           *                  - Behaviors
     19           *                  - Events
     20           *                  - Failure Flags
     21           *                  - Data Acquisition
     22           *
     23           *              Behaviors:
     24           *              Behaviors are executed by the motor or device. The Stop and Run Behaviors are
     25           *              standard behaviors that must be implemented by every motor controller for every
     26           *              motor or device. Any motor controller can define additional platform-specific
     27           *              behaviors.
     28           *
     29           *              Events:
     30           *              Events are generated by each motor or device in the system. The motor controller
     31           *              generates the events as they occur. Each time an event is generated, an event
     32           *              message is sent to the Client. There are standard events that every motor or
     33           *              device can generate. Any motor controller can define additional platform-specific
     34           *              events.
     35           *
     36           *              Failure Flags:
     37           *              TRUE/FALSE flags that are normally FALSE. When a failure is detected, the flag
     38           *              that corresponds to the failure is set to TRUE. The motor controller sets the
     39           *              Failure Flags as necessary. The Client has the ability to read the Failure Flags
     40           *              and request that all the flags be reset to FALSE.
     41           *
     42           *              Data Acquisition:
     43           *              The API provides some limited data acquisition features for platform-specific
     44           *              analog data channels. The client can choose the analog data channels to monitor
     45           *              and the rate at which the motor controller should publish the analog data. API221
     46           *              will use a single publication period for all the motors and their analog data
     47           *              values on the same motor controller.
     48           *
     49           * @copyright   Copyright 2016-2020 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     50           */
     51          
